JobDescription:
Overview

Now is the time to join us!

We’re Personify Health. We’re the first and only personalized health platform company to bring health, wellbeing, and navigation solutions together. Helping businesses optimize investments in their members while empowering people to meaningfully engage with their health. At Personify Health, we believe in offering total rewards, flexible opportunities, and a diverse inclusive community, where every voice matters. Together, we’re shaping a healthier, more engaged future.

Responsibilities

Data Engineer II sought by Personify Health for Providence, RI location. Telecommuting permitted.

Job Duties:
• Summary: Perform development activities within a data engineering team and help guide, onboard, and train Data Engineer I. Develop data pipelines and enhancements and investigate and troubleshoot issues, working closely with account management, ETL, data warehouse, business intelligence, and reporting teams. Work with multiple data structures, including relational and non-relational models. Do documentation, tech ops, sprints, implementation, monitor, QA, and related tasks.
• Extracting, cleansing, and loading data.
• Building data pipelines using SQL, Kafka, and other technologies.
• Investigation and documentation of new data sets.
• Triage incoming bugs and incidents.
• Perform technical operation tasks.
• Investigate and troubleshoot issues with data and data pipelines.
• Participation in sprint refinement, planning, and kick-off to help estimate stories, raise awareness and additional implementation details.
• Help monitor areas of the data pipeline and raise awareness to team when issues arise.
• Performing and implementing new quality assurance rules to maintain consistent and accurate data.

Qualifications

Job Requirements:
• Bachelor’s degree in Comp Sci, Comp Engr, Electronics Engr, IT, or related field, or foreign equivalent.
• Requires 2 years of relevant experience in data engineering.
• Must have skills via 2 years of experience in all of the following:
• examining data and code for quality and accuracy;
• modern relational and non-relational models;
• writing complex SQL, including pivots, window functions, and date calculations;
• Excel, Tableau, MicroStrategy, and PowerBI;
• REST API and JSON, and ability to parse that data and convert into relational models; and

Salary: $92,352.00 to $95,000.00 per year

Personify Health is an equal opportunity organization and is committed to diversity, inclusion, equity, and social justice.

We strive to cultivate a work environment where differences are celebrated, and employees of all backgrounds are empowered to thrive. Personify Health is committed to driving Diversity, Equity, Inclusion and Belonging (DEIB) for all stakeholders: employees (at each organization level), members, clients and the communities in which we operate. Diversity is core to who we are and critical to our work in health and wellbeing.

Beware of Hiring Scams: Personify Health will never ask for payment or sensitive personal information such as social security numbers during the hiring process. All official communication will come from a verified company email address. If you receive suspicious requests or communications, please report them to talent@personifyhealth.com. All of our legitimate openings can be found on the Personify Health Career Site.

Application Deadline: Open until position is filled.
Reasoning: The job description clearly states responsibilities related to data engineering tasks such as developing data pipelines, investigating data issues, and working with multiple data structures. These align with the typical functions of a Data Engineering division.
